SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 74
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor David McLain on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially recognize those outstanding
professionals who have devoted their careers to providing the highest-quality education and
learning environments for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is David McLain, who, having distinguished
himself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity throughout his career,
took his well-deserved retirement as director of schools for Greene County on January 31,
2025; and
WHEREAS, in 1997, Mr. McLain graduated from East Tennessee State University with a
Bachelor of Science Degree in Education, and he later received his Master of Arts in education
in 2006 from Union College; he also earned an Educational Specialist Degree from Lincoln
Memorial University in 2010; and
WHEREAS, Mr. McLain began his exemplary career as a teacher and coach at
Baileyton Elementary School; he later moved to North Greene High School, where he worked
as a teacher, coach, and athletic director; and
WHEREAS, as his career in education progressed, Mr. McLain worked his way up to
administration and served as the principal of North Greene High School for six years before
accepting the position of assistant director of operations and academic services and finally the
position of Greene County Director of Schools in 2015; and
WHEREAS, Mr. McLain truly served as an inspiration to the faculty, staff, and students
of Greene County Schools, and his friendship and counsel have always been highly valued by
those who are fortunate to know him; and
