WHEREAS, throughout his illustrious career, Mr. McLain has been fortunate to have the
love and support of his wife, Delana, and two sons, Dalton and Bennett; he is an active member
of New Lebanon Baptist Church, and he further serves his community as a coach of booster
club and Greeneville Parks and Recreation athletic teams; and
WHEREAS, David McLain is an extremely talented and compassionate administrator
who worked assiduously throughout his career in education to motivate his students, teachers,
and staff to reach their full potential as scholars, professionals, and citizens; and
WHEREAS, Mr. McLain epitomizes the dedicated professional who is wholly committed
to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and he should be specially
recognized on the occasion of his retirement; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Mr. David McLain upon his
exceptional service to Greene County as director of schools, salute his professional expertise
and personal excellence, and wish him much continued success and happiness during his
retirement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
